HEADWORD: Tibiotarsus
<hw>Tib`i*o*tar"sus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tibiotarsi</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The
large bone between the femur and tarsometatarsus in the leg of a bird.
It is formed by the union of the proximal part of the tarsus with the
tibia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

